1825
01:36:38,430 --> 01:36:40,069
We also added popping candy...

1826
01:36:40,070 --> 01:36:42,639
to express the feeling of excitement you get when you're in love,

1827
01:36:42,640 --> 01:36:44,200
like fireworks.

1828
01:36:44,500 --> 01:36:48,240
Thank you. Shall we dig in?

1829
01:36:49,070 --> 01:36:50,140
Thank you for the bread.

1830
01:36:50,280 --> 01:36:51,340
Thank you.

1831
01:36:53,850 --> 01:36:54,950
A moment, please.

1832
01:37:01,420 --> 01:37:02,860
We have perfume prepared as well.

1833
01:37:03,190 --> 01:37:04,260
Perfume?

1834
01:37:04,890 --> 01:37:05,890
Perfume?

1835
01:37:10,030 --> 01:37:11,200
This is the Heartbeat Perfume.

1836
01:37:16,500 --> 01:37:17,500
Thank you.

1837
01:37:19,710 --> 01:37:21,510
I was really nervous when they took out the perfume.

1838
01:37:21,610 --> 01:37:23,340
I thought it was a great idea.

1839
01:37:23,410 --> 01:37:26,349
Making edible perfume...

1840
01:37:26,350 --> 01:37:28,980
to add more fragrance to the bread was a very unique idea.

1841
01:37:29,450 --> 01:37:31,649
We thought citrus and fruity notes...

1842
01:37:31,650 --> 01:37:34,349
would go well with the babas.

1843
01:37:34,350 --> 01:37:35,890
So we added this perfume.

1844
01:37:40,160 --> 01:37:41,529
- I smell flowers. - Yes, roses.

1845
01:37:41,530 --> 01:37:43,030
- Flowers. - Rose water.

1846
01:37:46,670 --> 01:37:48,600
Then we'll sample the bread now.

1847
01:38:15,160 --> 01:38:17,330
Everything went well, just as we planned it.

1848
01:38:17,430 --> 01:38:20,269
I thought we would get a lot of points in this round.

1849
01:38:20,270 --> 01:38:22,970
I really hoped they would be happy with our dessert.

1850
01:38:35,880 --> 01:38:39,349
Their expression didn't change, and it was terrifying.

1851
01:38:39,350 --> 01:38:42,520
I had no idea what they were thinking.

1852
01:38:59,270 --> 01:39:01,770
What did you think, Masters?

1853
01:39:01,940 --> 01:39:05,939
I've never had baba in my life before today.

1854
01:39:05,940 --> 01:39:09,350
I wondered who came up with the idea to bake this.

1855
01:39:09,520 --> 01:39:13,289
Chef Dam Hyeon and Chef Dong Uk came up with the idea.

1856
01:39:13,290 --> 01:39:14,849
And the added kick with perfume...

1857
01:39:14,850 --> 01:39:17,590
was Chef Hwang Ji Oh's idea.

1858
01:39:17,860 --> 01:39:20,189
Baba is a cake made by soaking crunchy bread...

1859
01:39:20,190 --> 01:39:22,959
with sweet syrup and mixing the two harmoniously.

1860
01:39:22,960 --> 01:39:25,029
We thought this aspect was similar to flirting,

1861
01:39:25,030 --> 01:39:26,200
- and we chose baba as our product. - I see.

1862
01:39:26,800 --> 01:39:28,029
Should we pour this in now?

1863
01:39:28,030 --> 01:39:29,100
Sounds good.

1864
01:39:51,590 --> 01:39:53,259
I think this is innovative.

1865
01:39:53,260 --> 01:39:56,499
I'm sure many Koreans watching this...

1866
01:39:56,500 --> 01:39:58,129
have never heard of rum baba before.

1867
01:39:58,130 --> 01:39:59,830
They're going to start looking it up.

1868
01:39:59,970 --> 01:40:02,470
I applaud you for taking on this challenge.

1869
01:40:02,670 --> 01:40:03,970
It was a great choice.

1870
01:40:04,140 --> 01:40:06,339
Baba is going to trend in 2026.

1871
01:40:06,340 --> 01:40:07,340
Okay!

1872
01:40:07,570 --> 01:40:08,870
Great job, Edison!

1873
01:40:09,740 --> 01:40:11,040
Are you done flirting?

1874
01:40:11,140 --> 01:40:12,210
- Yes. - Great.

1875
01:40:12,850 --> 01:40:16,479
But you soaked the baba with syrup.

1876
01:40:16,480 --> 01:40:18,080
And about that...

1877
01:40:18,780 --> 01:40:21,419
You must've had a lot of discussions...

1878
01:40:21,420 --> 01:40:23,059
about how strong the alcohol should be,

1879
01:40:23,060 --> 01:40:25,519
or if it should be left in the bread at all.

1880
01:40:25,520 --> 01:40:26,660
How did you decide that?

1881
01:40:26,830 --> 01:40:29,059
Personally, I thought...

1882
01:40:29,060 --> 01:40:31,359
we should take the rum out completely.

1883
01:40:31,360 --> 01:40:34,170
But my other teammates thought...

1884
01:40:34,300 --> 01:40:36,770
rum baba should have rum in it.

1885
01:40:37,070 --> 01:40:38,339
And we all thought...

1886
01:40:38,340 --> 01:40:41,969
that leaving a hint of rum would be better.

1887
01:40:41,970 --> 01:40:45,339
So we reduced the amount of rum by half.

1888
01:40:45,340 --> 01:40:46,450
Then...

1889
01:40:51,920 --> 01:40:52,990
you shouldn't have put it in at all.

1890
01:40:55,490 --> 01:40:57,589
Or if you decided to put the rum in...

1891
01:40:57,590 --> 01:40:59,219
and boil all the alcohol away,

1892
01:40:59,220 --> 01:41:01,029
the aroma of the rum would still be here.

1893
01:41:01,030 --> 01:41:02,899
That would have helped...

1894
01:41:02,900 --> 01:41:04,430
with the greasiness of the cream.

1895
01:41:05,730 --> 01:41:08,469
I was the villain in our team...

1896
01:41:08,470 --> 01:41:11,840
arguing that we shouldn't put alcohol in at all.

1897
01:41:11,900 --> 01:41:14,470
How about just a little bit of whiskey?

1898
01:41:14,810 --> 01:41:16,380
Whiskey? No way.

1899
01:41:16,910 --> 01:41:18,180
- Why not? - I vote against alcohol.

1900
01:41:18,240 --> 01:41:19,240
Really?

1901
01:41:20,350 --> 01:41:22,749
- I never use alcohol when baking. - I see.

1902
01:41:22,750 --> 01:41:25,379
That's just me, but if you guys want to...

1903
01:41:25,380 --> 01:41:26,419
we could put it in.

1904
01:41:26,420 --> 01:41:28,289
But if you're so set against it,

1905
01:41:28,290 --> 01:41:29,860
we should reduce the amount.

1906
01:41:30,220 --> 01:41:31,420
I felt so sorry to my teammates.

1907
01:41:33,130 --> 01:41:35,630
Master Cha Seung Hee, what did you think?

1908
01:41:35,930 --> 01:41:38,399
I thought the presentation was very nice,

1909
01:41:38,400 --> 01:41:41,329
especially considering the theme, flirting.

1910
01:41:41,330 --> 01:41:43,299
But when I first took a bite,

1911
01:41:43,300 --> 01:41:47,169
I thought the flavor of the rum and the cream on top...

1912
01:41:47,170 --> 01:41:50,040
wasn't strong enough to be flirting.

1913
01:41:51,640 --> 01:41:55,110
I personally think the rum was a complete waste of money.

1914
01:41:55,450 --> 01:41:57,579
If you were going to use rum,

1915
01:41:57,580 --> 01:41:59,220
you should have made it stronger.

1916
01:41:59,380 --> 01:42:01,590
Being bolder might have been better.

1917
01:42:01,620 --> 01:42:02,890
You were too careful.

1918
01:42:04,120 --> 01:42:05,860
Yes, you guys were too cautious.

1919
01:42:08,730 --> 01:42:10,599
But this works for lightweights like me.

1920
01:42:10,600 --> 01:42:12,660
I thought it was great.

1921
01:42:15,130 --> 01:42:17,969
Now, will the Masters...

1922
01:42:17,970 --> 01:42:19,470
put up your scores?

1923
01:42:20,610 --> 01:42:23,280
- Delivery! - Goodness.

1924
01:42:24,180 --> 01:42:25,910
I'm quite confident. Yes.

1925
01:42:30,720 --> 01:42:31,720
We're in trouble.

1926
01:42:31,850 --> 01:42:34,949
One is too bland, the other is too salty.

1927
01:42:34,950 --> 01:42:36,560
It tasted a bit rubbery too.

1928
01:42:36,820 --> 01:42:39,190
We may have failed to meet their expectations.

1929
01:42:39,260 --> 01:42:40,889
Although I liked the concept,

1930
01:42:40,890 --> 01:42:42,189
I was disappointed with the flavor.

1931
01:42:42,190 --> 01:42:43,899
The flavors were all over the place.

1932
01:42:43,900 --> 01:42:44,930
It's a waste of money.

1933
01:42:45,660 --> 01:42:47,030
They're really strict.

1934
01:42:48,600 --> 01:42:49,939
Everyone in that team will fail,

1935
01:42:49,940 --> 01:42:53,040
and they will leave the bread factory immediately.

1936
01:42:53,470 --> 01:42:54,669
Anything but the last place.

1937
01:42:54,670 --> 01:42:56,539
I didn't want to be the cause of my team failing.

1938
01:42:56,540 --> 01:42:58,440
I really didn't want to be in last place.

1939
01:43:00,180 --> 01:43:02,049
Oh, no, I'm so nervous.

1940
01:43:02,050 --> 01:43:03,650
What for? We're going to pass.
